JOB SUMMARY: Nursing skills will be monitored by Director of Nursing for quality assurance under the direct supervision of the SHEP Nursing Manager and LVN Supervisor, the LVN shall:

ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS:
1) Provide Skill nursing care to STD patients in a clinical setting at the Center WeHo and the STD Clinic if primary STD LVN is out of the office; monitor and respond to patient portal messages to provider.
2) Assist in the coordination of patient flow through the STD clinic to maximize the time of service providers; triage and triage patients to provider/nursing as appropriate, room and vital patients as needed.
3) Contact all client including those tested at offside locations and clients testing during clinic hours regarding positive STD test results, disclose results and make appointment, respond to patient’s inquiries regarding lab results by phone, email or patient portal.
4) Follow-up calls to pharmacy if electronic submission is not received, call in verbal orders, call in prescriptions needing verbal order, check fax refills request, print and take to provider to sign and fax back. Assist with prior authorization. Respond to patient questions about refills and pharmacy requests, including patients accessing prescription through PAP.
5) Update pharmacy log book, restock med cabinet, and deliver medication orders to pharmacist.
6) Before each clinic session, stock and set up exam room; monitor refrigerators, prepare equipment for procedures/treatments.
7) During STD clinic, administer medications to clients within scope of practice of the license, provide patient education regarding medications, diagnosis and prevention with specific regards to STDs, provide patient referrals, book follow-up appointments when necessary and assist provider when necessary.
8) Document medication administered, observe patients, document and reports any medications side effects.
9) Assist physicians and mid-level providers in performing specialized procedures.
10) Assist in lab as needed, oversee PrEP Medical Assistant and duties performed.
11) Administer vaccines. Complete necessary documentation regarding vaccinations.
12) Collaborate with staff on literature and other written information.
13) Attend offside testing efforts at festivals and health fairs.
14) Participate in staff meetings, agency meetings, planning meetings and other meetings as needed;
15) Other duties as assigned;

JOB QUALIFICATIONS AND EXPERIENCE:
1) Knowledge of or experience working with the LGBTQ community and familiarity with issues of particular relevance to LGBTQ people;
2) A passion for the Center’s work and its mission to make the world a better place for LGBTQ people;
3) Requires current California LVN License;
4) Current AHA CPR certification;
5) STI and HIV/AIDS healthcare and treatment/adherence experience preferred;
6) Basic knowledge of infectious diseases and state/federal reporting requirements;
7) Ability to handle multiple tasks, is detail oriented and maintains strict confidentiality of medical information;
8) Excellent verbal and written communication skills, including strong organizational, detail and interpersonal skills;
9) Computer skills and knowledge including word processing, database operations, spreadsheets, and other software systems;
10) Bilingual (English/Spanish) skills, a plus;
11) Demonstrated ability to work effectively with people of diverse races, ethnicities, nationalities, sexual orientations, gender identities, gender expression, socio-economic backgrounds, religions, ages, English-speaking abilities, immigration statuses, and physical abilities in a multicultural environment.

To Apply: Please submit a cover letter and resume.

The Los Angeles LGBT Center is an Equal Opportunity Employer and is committed to fostering diversity within its staff. Applications are encouraged from all persons regardless of their race, color, ancestry, religious creed, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, medical/physical/mental condition, pregnancy/childbirth and related medical condition, age, marital status, or veteran status.
